<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏘️ Builder Basics — Complete Your Village (Extension)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Bring It All Together · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Type:</strong> Extension Activity · <strong>Time:</strong> about 60 minutes</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧩 This is a bonus challenge, not a weekly lesson. Try it after the Week 8 village project, once you can build with loops and move the agent between spots.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · The Challenge 🎯</h2>
<p>Your village has a good start, but a real village needs more than walls. <strong>Complete your village</strong> so it feels like a place someone could live.</p>
<p>By the end, your village must have <strong>all four</strong> of these:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🏠 A <strong>house with a roof</strong>
🪣 A <strong>well</strong>
💧 A <strong>small pond</strong>
🌸 A <strong>small flower bed</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p>There is no fixed size and no map. <strong>You</strong> decide how big each thing is and where it goes. One rule you must not break:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>⚠️ <strong>Everything must be built with code.</strong> No placing blocks by hand — every wall, flower, and drop of water goes down because the agent ran your commands.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>In your own words, what four things must your village have when you finish?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why do you think we say "build it with code" instead of placing blocks by hand?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Plan Before You Build ✏️</h2>
<p>A builder plans first. For <strong>each</strong> of the four structures, decide what it is made of and how big. Think about the blocks and whether you need a loop.</p>
<p><strong>House with a roof</strong> — What blocks? How wide and how tall? Where does the roof sit?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Well</strong> — What shape is the hole? What goes around the top? Is there water inside?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Small pond</strong> — How will you make the dip in the ground? What fills it?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Small flower bed</strong> — What holds the soil? How many flowers, and how will you place a row of them?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Think in Loops 🔁</h2>
<p>You built walls with loops before. A loop is for anything you do <strong>again and again</strong> — a row of wall blocks, a row of flowers, the four sides of a well.</p>
<p><strong>Which of your four structures will use a loop, and what does the loop repeat each time?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p>Between one structure and the next, the agent has to <strong>walk to a new spot</strong> so nothing lands on top of the last build.</p>
<p><strong>Between the house and the pond, what will the agent do to get to a clean spot?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Now go to your homework world and build. Run your code for each structure, one at a time, and move the agent between them. Keep going until your village has <strong>the house with a roof, the well, the small pond, and the small flower bed</strong> — all placed by code.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
